    <!-- 01 · Florida Keys -->
    <div class="chapter" id="ch-0" style="display:none">
      <div class="ch-left">
        <div class="ch-kicker">
          <span class="ch-num">01</span>
          Florida Keys <span class="yr">&middot; before everything</span>
        </div>
        <h2 class="ch-title">Where I&rsquo;m from.</h2>
        <div class="ch-body">
          <p>
            Islamorada, Florida Keys. A chain of islands with one road in and one road
            out, 45 minutes from the nearest major city.
          </p>
          <p>
            Hurricane season taught me to plan for the worst and hope for the best. Living on an
            island taught me the rest is rarely an emergency. Those ideals carried over into the way I live
            my life and my career: clear priorities when something breaks, perspective on
            everything else.
          </p>
          <p>
            Four years at Coral Shores High School ended as co-captain of the swim team,
            competing at the district and regional levels in the 200m freestyle and
            100m butterfly.
          </p>
